  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375 degrees F.",
    "In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium-high heat. Add onions and cook until translucent, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add garlic and cook for another minute.",
    "Stir in carrots and celery. Cook for an additional 2-3 minutes or until vegetables start to soften.",
    "Pour in tomato sauce and vegetable broth. Bring to a boil then reduce heat to low. Simmer for 10-15 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
    "Add nutritional yeast, basil, oregano, salt, and pepper. Stir well. Cook for another 5 minutes or until thickened slightly.",
    "Remove from heat. Let cool slightly before using as a filling in tamales."
